{
  "texts": [
    "For prompting-based LLM, FP cases take more than one third.",
    "As low precision in domainspecific NER is a crucial problem (Dai, 2021; Karim et al., 2023) and FP constitute a significant proportion across all three models, we focus on correcting the FP cases from the initial predictions.",
    "By doing so, we can boost the NER performance regardless of the model that comes beforehand.",
    "To gain clues on how to resolve the errors, we examine where existing models fall short to make precise predictions.",
    "Among the FP cases, we take a closer look on errors (i.e., Type, Span, and T&S) where the models' predictions partially overlap with the gold annotation, but either the type or span is incorrect."
  ]
}